Inside the border object, we're going to modify all border styles.

32
00:02:16.330 --> 00:02:20.770
First, let's set the width property to two x.

33
00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:27.080
Afterward set the radius property to ten x.

34
00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:32.730
Next set the style property to solid.

35
00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:42.070
Lastly, let's set the colour property to the WP preset color u primary variable.

36
00:02:47.390 --> 00:02:51.320
As you can tell, the values for these properties must be valid.

37
00:02:51.350 --> 00:02:52.760
CSS values.

38
00:02:52.790 --> 00:02:55.500
Time to test our code in your browser.

39
00:02:55.520 --> 00:02:58.640
Try adding the code block to the template.

40
00:03:04.380 --> 00:03:08.250
After adding this block, our default stylings have been applied.

41
00:03:08.280 --> 00:03:11.810
If users don't like the styles, that's perfectly fine.

42
00:03:11.820 --> 00:03:17.770
The border settings are freely modifiable from the sidebar by enabling all border settings.

43
00:03:17.790 --> 00:03:22.980
Users can modify the width, color, style and radius of a border.

44
